We solve it using an &quot;archive&quot; collection in mongodb. Deleting moves a document from one collection to the archive, while undo moves it back.<p>We also implement ability to find deleted documents by id, by searching the archive if the record is not found in the original collection.<p>API looks like this:<p><pre><code>    // delete something
    delete(&quot;/products/123&quot;)

    // see it in the archive
    get(&quot;/archive/products/123&quot;)

    // undelete it
    put(&quot;/products/123&quot;, {$restore: true})</code></pre>
